                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-30T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 30—5:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. American consul at Swatow telegraphs that Swatow authorities have instituted
                    oil monopoly similar to that in operation at Canton—see Canton’s despatch 366,
                    October 27th, to Department.<note n="92" xml:id="d846fn92">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
